#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You create an invisible sensor within range in a location familiar to you (a "
"place you have visited or seen before) or in an obvious location that is "
"unfamiliar to you (such as behind a door, around a corner, or in a grove of "
"trees). The sensor remains in place for the duration, and it can't be "
"attacked or otherwise interacted with.    \n"
"When you cast the spell, you choose seeing or hearing. You can use the "
"chosen sense through the sensor as if you were in its space. As your action, "
"you can switch between seeing and hearing.    \n"
"A creature that can see the sensor (such as a creature benefiting from "
"**_see invisibility_** or truesight) sees a luminous, intangible orb about "
"the size of your fist. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:903
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/clone.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:908
msgid "name: Clone level: 8 school: necromancy classes: wizard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:911
msgid "# Clone _8th-level necromancy_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:916
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 hour    \n"
"**Range:** Touch    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp and at least 1 "
"cubic inch of flesh of the creature that is to be cloned, which the spell "
"consumes, and a vessel worth at least 2,000 gp that has a sealable lid and "
"is large enough to hold a Medium creature, such as a huge urn, coffin, mud- "
"filled cyst in the ground, or crystal container filled with salt water)    "
"\n"
"**Duration:** Instantaneous \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:919
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This spell grows an inert duplicate of a living creature as a safeguard "
"against death. This clone forms inside a sealed vessel and grows to full "
"size and maturity after 120 days; you can also choose to have the clone be a "
"younger version of the same creature. It remains inert and endures "
"indefinitely, as long as its vessel remains undisturbed.    \n"
"At any time after the clone matures, if the original creature dies, its soul "
"transfers to the clone, provided that the soul is free and willing to "
"return. The clone is physically identical to the original and has the same "
"personality, memories, and abilities, but none of the original's "
"equipment. The original creature's physical remains, if they still exist, "
"become inert and can't thereafter be restored to life, since the creature's "
"soul is elsewhere. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:921
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/cloudkill.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:927
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Cloudkill\n"
"level: 5\n"
"school: conjuration\n"
"classes: sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:930
msgid "# Cloudkill _5th-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:935
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 120 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S   \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:939
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You create a 20-foot-radius sphere of poisonous, yellow-green fog centered "
"on a point you choose within range. The fog spreads around corners. It lasts "
"for the duration or until strong wind disperses the fog, ending the "
"spell. Its area is heavily obscured.    \n"
"When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or "
"starts its turn there, that creature must make a Constitution saving "
"throw. The creature takes 5d8 poison damage on a failed save, or half as "
"much damage on a successful one. Creatures are affected even if they hold "
"their breath or don't need to breathe.    \n"
"The fog moves 10 feet away from you at the start of each of your turns, "
"rolling along the surface of the ground. The vapors, being heavier than air, "
"sink to the lowest level of the land, even pouring down openings. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:941 translations/spells.merged.md:1093
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th "
"level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above "
"5th. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:943
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/color_spray.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:949
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Color Spray\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: illusion\n"
"classes: sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:952
msgid "# Color Spray _1st-level illusion_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:957
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action   \n"
"**Range:** Self (15-foot cone)   \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a pinch of powder or sand that is colored red, "
"yellow, and blue)    \n"
"**Duration:** 1 round \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:960
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A dazzling array of flashing, colored light springs from your hand. Roll "
"6d10; the total is how many hit points of creatures this spell can "
"effect. Creatures in a 15-foot cone originating from you are affected in "
"ascending order of their current hit points (ignoring unconscious creatures "
"and creatures that can't see).    \n"
"Starting with the creature that has the lowest current hit points, each "
"creature affected by this spell is blinded until the spell ends. Subtract "
"each creature's hit points from the total before moving on to the creature "
"with the next lowest hit points. A creature's hit points must be equal to or "
"less than the remaining total for that creature to be affected. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:962
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd "
"level or higher, roll an additional 2d10 for each slot level above 1st. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:964
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/command.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:970
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Command\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: enchantment\n"
"classes: cleric\n"
"         paladin\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:973
msgid "# Command _1st-level enchantment_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:978
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action   \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V   \n"
"**Duration:** 1 round   \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:986
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You speak a one-word command to a creature you can see within range. The "
"target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or follow the command on its "
"next turn. The spell has no effect if the target is undead, if it doesn't "
"understand your language, or if your command is directly harmful to it.    "
"\n"
"Some typical commands and their effects follow. You might issue a command "
"other than one described here. If you do so, the GM determines how the "
"target behaves. If the target can't follow your command, the spell ends.    "
"\n"
"**Approach.** The target moves toward you by the shortest and most direct "
"route, ending its turn if it moves within 5 feet of you.    \n"
"**Drop.** The target drops whatever it is holding and then ends its turn.    "
"\n"
"**Flee.** The target spends its turn moving away from you by the fastest "
"available means.   \n"
"**Grovel.** The target falls prone and then ends its turn.   \n"
"**Halt.** The target doesn't move and takes no actions. A flying creature "
"stays aloft, provided that it is able to do so. If it must move to stay "
"aloft, it flies the minimum distance needed to remain in the air. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:988
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd "
"level or higher, you can affect one additional creature for each slot level "
"above 1st. The creatures must be within 30 feet of each other when you "
"target them.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:990
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/commune.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:995
msgid "name: Commune level: 5 school: divination classes: cleric"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:998
msgid "# Commune _5th-level divination (ritual)_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1003
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 minute    \n"
"**Range:** Self    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (incense and a vial of holy or unholy water)    \n"
"**Duration:** 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1007
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You contact your deity or a divine proxy and ask up to three questions that "
"can be answered with a yes or no. You must ask your questions before the "
"spell ends. You receive a correct answer for each question.    \n"
"Divine beings aren't necessarily omniscient, so you might receive "
"\"unclear\" as an answer if a question pertains to information that lies "
"beyond the deity's knowledge. In a case where a one-word answer could be "
"misleading or contrary to the deity's interests, the GM might offer a short "
"phrase as an answer instead.    \n"
"If you cast the spell two or more times before finishing your next long "
"rest, there is a cumulative 25 percent chance for each casting after the "
"first that you get no answer. The GM makes this roll in secret. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1009
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/commune_with_nature.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1015
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Commune with Nature\n"
"level: 5\n"
"school: divination\n"
"classes: druid\n"
"         ranger\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1018
msgid "# Commune with Nature _5th-level divination (ritual)_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1023
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 minute    \n"
"**Range:** Self    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Instantaneous \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1026
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You briefly become one with nature and gain knowledge of the surrounding "
"territory. In the outdoors, the spell gives you knowledge of the land within "
"3 miles of you. In caves and other natural underground settings, the radius "
"is limited to 300 feet. The spell doesn't function where nature has been "
"replaced by construction, such as in dungeons and towns.    \n"
"You instantly gain knowledge of up to three facts of your choice about any "
"of the following subjects as they relate to the area:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1032
msgid "terrain and bodies of water"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1032
msgid "prevalent plants, minerals, animals, or peoples"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1032
msgid "powerful celestials, fey, fiends, elementals, or undead"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1032
msgid "influence from other planes of existence"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1032
msgid "buildings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1034
msgid ""
"For example, you could determine the location of powerful undead in the "
"area, the location of major sources of safe drinking water, and the location "
"of any nearby towns."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1036
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/comprehend_languages.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1044
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Comprehend Languages\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: divination\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         warlock\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1047
msgid "# Comprehend Languages _1st-level divination (ritual)_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1052
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Self    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a pinch of soot and salt)    \n"
"**Duration:** 1 hour \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1055
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For the duration, you understand the literal meaning of any spoken language "
"that you hear. You also understand any written language that you see, but "
"you must be touching the surface on which the words are written. It takes "
"about 1 minute to read one page of text.    \n"
"This spell doesn't decode secret messages in a text or a glyph, such as an "
"arcane sigil, that isn't part of a written language. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1057
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/compulsion.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1062
msgid "name: Compulsion level: 4 school: enchantment classes: bard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1065
msgid "# Compulsion _4th-level enchantment_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1070 translations/spells.merged.md:4529
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 30 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1073
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Creatures of your choice that you can see within range and that can hear you "
"must make a Wisdom saving throw. A target automatically succeeds on this "
"saving throw if it can't be charmed. On a failed save, a target is affected "
"by this spell. Until the spell ends, you can use a bonus action on each of "
"your turns to designate a direction that is horizontal to you. Each affected "
"target must use as much of its movement as possible to move in that "
"direction on its next turn. It can take its action before it moves. After "
"moving in this way, it can make another Wisdom saving to try to end the "
"effect.    \n"
"A target isn't compelled to move into an obviously deadly hazard, such as a "
"fire or pit, but it will provoke opportunity attacks to move in the "
"designated direction.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1075
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/cone_of_cold.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1081
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Cone of Cold\n"
"level: 5\n"
"school: evocation\n"
"classes: sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1083
msgid "_5th-level evocation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1088
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Self (60-foot cone)    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a small crystal or glass cone)    \n"
"**Duration:** Instantaneous \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1091
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A blast of cold air erupts from your hands. Each creature in a 60-foot cone "
"must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes 8d8 cold damage on a "
"failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.    \n"
"A creature killed by this spell becomes a frozen statue until it thaws. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1095
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/confusion.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1103
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Confusion\n"
"level: 4\n"
"school: enchantment\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         druid\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1106
msgid "# Confusion _4th-level enchantment_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1111
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 90 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (three nut shells)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1114
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This spell assaults and twists creatures' minds, spawning delusions and "
"provoking uncontrolled action. Each creature in a 10-foot-radius sphere "
"centered on a point you choose within range must succeed on a Wisdom saving "
"throw when you cast this spell or be affected by it.    \n"
"An affected target can't take reactions and must roll a d10 at the start of "
"each of its turns to determine its behavior for that turn. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1121
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| d10  | Behavior |\n"
"|------|----------|\n"
"| 1    | The creature uses all its movement to move in a random "
"direction. To determine the direction, roll a d8 and assign a direction to "
"each die face. The creature doesn't take an action this turn. |\n"
"| 2-6  | The creature doesn't move or take actions this turn.  |\n"
"| 7-8  | The creature uses its action to make a melee attack against a "
"randomly determined creature within its reach. If there is no creature "
"within its reach, the creature does nothing this turn. |\n"
"| 9-10 | The creature can act and move normally. |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1123
msgid ""
"At the end of each of its turns, an affected target can make a Wisdom saving "
"throw. If it succeeds, this effect ends for that target."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1125
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th "
"level or higher, the radius of the sphere increases by 5 feet for each slot "
"level above 4th. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1127
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/conjure_animals.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1133
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Conjure Animals\n"
"level: 3\n"
"school: conjuration\n"
"classes: druid\n"
"         ranger\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1136
msgid "# Conjure Animals _3rd-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1141 translations/spells.merged.md:2023
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 hour \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1143
msgid ""
"You summon fey spirits that take the form of beasts and appear in unoccupied "
"spaces that you can see within range. Choose one of the following options "
"for what appears:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1148
msgid "One beast of challenge rating 2 or lower"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1148
msgid "Two beasts of challenge rating 1 or lower"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1148
msgid "Four beasts of challenge rating 1/2 or lower"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1148
msgid "Eight beasts of challenge rating 1/4 or lower"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1152
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each beast is also considered fey, and it disappears when it drops to 0 hit "
"points or when the spell ends.    \n"
"The summoned creatures are friendly to you and your companions. Roll "
"initiative for the summoned creatures as a group, which has its own "
"turns. They obey any verbal commands that you issue to them (no action "
"required by you). If you don't issue any commands to them, they defend "
"themselves from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.    \n"
"The GM has the creatures' statistics. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1154
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using certain higher-level "
"spell slots, you choose one of the summoning options above, and more "
"creatures appear: twice as many with a 5th-level slot, three times as many "
"with a 7th-level slot, and four times as many with a 9th-level slot. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1156
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/conjure_celestial.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1161
msgid "name: Conjure Celestial level: 7 school: conjuration classes: cleric"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1164
msgid "# Conjure Celestial _7th-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1169 translations/spells.merged.md:1213 translations/spells.merged.md:1236
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 minute    \n"
"**Range:** 90 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 hour \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1173
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You summon a celestial of challenge rating 4 or lower, which appears in an "
"unoccupied space that you can see within range. The celestial disappears "
"when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.    \n"
"The celestial is friendly to you and your companions for the duration. Roll "
"initiative for the celestial, which has its own turns. It obeys any verbal "
"commands that you issue to it (no action required by you), as long as they "
"don't violate its alignment. If you don't issue any commands to the "
"celestial, it defends itself from hostile creatures but otherwise takes no "
"actions.    \n"
"The GM has the celestial's statistics. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1175
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a 9th-level spell slot, "
"you summon a celestial of challenge rating 5 or lower. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1177
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/conjure_elemental.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1183
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Conjure Elemental\n"
"level: 5\n"
"school: conjuration\n"
"classes: druid\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1186
msgid "# Conjure Elemental _5th-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1191
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 minute    \n"
"**Range:** 90 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (burning incense for air, soft clay for earth, "
"sulfur and phosphorus for fire, or water and sand for water)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 hour \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1195
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You call forth an elemental servant. Choose an area of air, earth, fire, or "
"water that fills a 10-foot cube within range. An elemental of challenge "
"rating 5 or lower appropriate to the area you chose appears in an unoccupied "
"space within 10 feet of it. For example, a fire elemental emerges from a "
"bonfire, and an earth elemental rises up from the ground. The elemental "
"disappears when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.    \n"
"The elemental is friendly to you and your companions for the duration. Roll "
"initiative for the elemental, which has its own turns. It obeys any verbal "
"commands that you issue to it (no action required by you). If you don't "
"issue any commands to the elemental, it defends itself from hostile "
"creatures but otherwise takes no actions.    \n"
"If your concentration is broken, the elemental doesn't disappear. Instead, "
"you lose control of the elemental, it becomes hostile toward you and your "
"companions, and it might attack. An uncontrolled elemental can't be "
"dismissed by you, and it disappears 1 hour after you summoned it. The GM has "
"the elemental's statistics. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1197
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th "
"level or higher, the challenge rating increases by 1 for each slot level "
"above 5th. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1199
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/conjure_fey.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:1205
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Conjure Fey\n"
"level: 6\n"
"school: conjuration\n"
