#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Eyebite\n"
"level: 6\n"
"school: necromancy\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         warlock\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2286
msgid "# Eyebite _6th-level necromancy_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2291 translations/spells.merged.md:6400 translations/spells.merged.md:6528
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Self    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2296
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"For the spell's duration, your eyes become an inky void imbued with dread "
"power. One creature of your choice within 60 feet of you that you can see "
"must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be affected by one of the following "
"effects of your choice for the duration. On each of your turns until the "
"spell ends, you can use your action to target another creature but can't "
"target a creature again if it has succeeded on a saving throw against this "
"casting of **_eyebite_**.    \n"
"**Asleep.** The target falls unconscious. It wakes up if it takes any damage "
"or if another creature uses its action to shake the sleeper awake.    \n"
"**Panicked.** The target is frightened of you. On each of its turns, the "
"frightened creature must take the Dash action and move away from you by the "
"safest and shortest available route, unless there is nowhere to move. If the "
"target moves to a place at least 60 feet away from you where it can no "
"longer see you, this effect ends.    \n"
"**Sickened.** The target has disadvantage on attack rolls and ability "
"checks. At the end of each of its turns, it can make another Wisdom saving "
"throw. If it succeeds, the effect ends.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2298
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/fabricate.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2303
msgid "name: Fabricate level: 4 school: transmutation classes: wizard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2306
msgid "# Fabricate _4th-level transmutation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2311
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 10 minutes    \n"
"**Range:** 120 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Instantaneous \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2315
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You convert raw materials into products of the same material. For example, "
"you can fabricate a wooden bridge from a clump of trees, a rope from a patch "
"of hemp, and clothes from flax or wool.    \n"
"Choose raw materials that you can see within range. You can fabricate a "
"Large or smaller object (contained within a 10-foot cube, or eight connected "
"5-foot cubes), given a sufficient quantity of raw material. If you are "
"working with metal, stone, or another mineral substance, however, the "
"fabricated object can be no larger than Medium (contained within a single "
"5-foot cube). The quality of objects made by the spell is commensurate with "
"the quality of the raw materials.    \n"
"Creatures or magic items can't be created or transmuted by this spell. You "
"also can't use it to create items that ordinarily require a high degree of "
"craftsmanship, such as jewelry, weapons, glass, or armor, unless you have "
"proficiency with the type of artisan's tools used to craft such objects. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2317
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/faerie_fire.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2323
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Faerie Fire\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: evocation\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         druid\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2326
msgid "# Faerie Fire _1st-level evocation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2331
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2334
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Each object in a 20-foot cube within range is outlined in blue, green, or "
"violet light (your choice). Any creature in the area when the spell is cast "
"is also outlined in light if it fails a Dexterity saving throw. For the "
"duration, objects and affected creatures shed dim light in a 10-foot "
"radius.    \n"
"Any attack roll against an affected creature or object has advantage if the "
"attacker can see it, and the affected creature or object can't benefit from "
"being invisible.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2336
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/faithful_hound.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2341
msgid "name: Faithful Hound level: 4 school: conjuration classes: wizard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2344
msgid "# Faithful Hound _4th-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2349
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 30 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a tiny silver whistle, a piece of bone, and a "
"thread)    \n"
"**Duration:** 8 hours \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2353
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You conjure a phantom watchdog in an unoccupied space that you can see "
"within range, where it remains for the duration, until you dismiss it as an "
"action, or until you move more than 100 feet away from it.    \n"
"The hound is invisible to all creatures except you and can't be harmed. When "
"a Small or larger creature comes within 30 feet of it without first speaking "
"the password that you specify when you cast this spell, the hound starts "
"barking loudly. The hound sees invisible creatures and can see into the "
"Ethereal Plane. It ignores illusions.    \n"
"At the start of each of your turns, the hound attempts to bite one creature "
"within 5 feet of it that is hostile to you. The hound's attack bonus is "
"equal to your spellcasting ability modifier + your proficiency bonus. On a "
"hit, it deals 4d8 piercing damage. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2355
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/false_life.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:2361
#, no-wrap
