"name: Move Earth\n"
"level: 6\n"
"school: transmutation\n"
"classes: druid\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:4571
msgid "# Move Earth _6th-level transmutation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:4576
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 120 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (an iron blade and a small bag containing a mixture "
"of soils--clay, loam, and sand)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 2 hours \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:4582
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Choose an area of terrain no larger than 40 feet on a side within range. You "
"can reshape dirt, sand, or clay in the area in any manner you choose for the "
"duration. You can raise or lower the area's elevation, create or fill in a "
"trench, erect or flatten a wall, or form a pillar. The extent of any such "
"changes can't exceed half the area's largest dimension. So, if you affect a "
"40-foot square, you can create a pillar up to 20 feet high, raise or lower "
"the square's elevation by up to 20 feet, dig a trench up to 20 feet deep, "
"and so on. It takes 10 minutes for these changes to complete.    \n"
"At the end of every 10 minutes you spend concentrating on the spell, you can "
"choose a new area of terrain to affect.    \n"
"Because the terrain's transformation occurs slowly, creatures in the area "
"can't usually be trapped or injured by the ground's movement.    \n"
"This spell can't manipulate natural stone or stone construction. Rocks and "
"structures shift to accommodate the new terrain. If the way you shape the "
"terrain would make a structure unstable, it might collapse.    \n"
"Similarly, this spell doesn't directly affect plant growth. The moved earth "
"carries any plants along with it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:4584
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/nondetection.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:4591
