"level: 2\n"
"school: evocation\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         warlock\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5613
msgid "# Shatter _2nd-level evocation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5618
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a chip of mica)    \n"
"**Duration:** Instantaneous \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5621
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A sudden loud ringing noise, painfully intense, erupts from a point of your "
"choice within range. Each creature in a 10-foot-radius sphere centered on "
"that point must make a Constitution saving throw. A creature takes 3d8 "
"thunder damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful "
"one. A creature made of inorganic material such as stone, crystal, or metal "
"has disadvantage on this saving throw.    \n"
"A nonmagical object that isn't being worn or carried also takes the damage "
"if it's in the spell's area. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5625
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/shield.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5631
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Shield\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: abjuration\n"
"classes: sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5634
msgid "# Shield _1st-level abjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5639
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 reaction, which you take when you are hit by an attack "
"or targeted by the magic missile spell    \n"
"**Range:** Self    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** 1 round \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5641
msgid ""
"An invisible barrier of magical force appears and protects you. Until the "
"start of your next turn, you have a +5 bonus to AC, including against the "
"triggering attack, and you take no damage from **_magic missile_**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5643
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/shield_of_faith.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5649
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Shield of Faith\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: abjuration\n"
"classes: cleric\n"
"         paladin\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5652
msgid "# Shield of Faith _1st-level abjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5657
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 bonus action    \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a small parchment with a bit of holy text written "
"on it)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5659
msgid ""
"A shimmering field appears and surrounds a creature of your choice within "
"range, granting it a +2 bonus to AC for the duration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5661
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/shillelagh.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5666
msgid "name: Shillelagh level: 0 school: transmutation classes: druid"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5669
msgid "# Shillelagh _Transmutation cantrip_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5674
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 bonus action    \n"
"**Range:** Touch    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (mistletoe, a shamrock leaf, and a club or "
"quarterstaff)    \n"
"**Duration:** 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5676
msgid ""
"The wood of a club or quarterstaff you are holding is imbued with nature's "
"power. For the duration, you can use your spellcasting ability instead of "
"Strength for the attack and damage rolls of melee attacks using that weapon, "
"and the weapon's damage die becomes a d8. The weapon also becomes magical, "
"if it isn't already. The spell ends if you cast it again or if you let go of "
"the weapon."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5678
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/shocking_grasp.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5684
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Shocking Grasp\n"
"level: 0\n"
"school: evocation\n"
"classes: sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5687
msgid "# Shocking Grasp _Evocation cantrip_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5695
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Lightning springs from your hand to deliver a shock to a creature you try to "
"touch. Make a melee spell attack against the target. You have advantage on "
"the attack roll if the target is wearing armor made of metal. On a hit, the "
"target takes 1d8 lightning damage, and it can't take reactions until the "
"start of its next turn.    \n"
"The spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th "
"level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8). \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5697
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/silence.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5704
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Silence\n"
"level: 2\n"
"school: illusion\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         cleric\n"
"         ranger\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5707
msgid "# Silence _2nd-level illusion (ritual)_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5712
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 120 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5714
msgid ""
"For the duration, no sound can be created within or pass through a "
"20-foot-radius sphere centered on a point you choose within range. Any "
"creature or object entirely inside the sphere is immune to thunder damage, "
"and creatures are deafened while entirely inside it. Casting a spell that "
"includes a verbal component is impossible there."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5716
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/silent_image.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5723
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Silent Image\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: illusion\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5726
msgid "# Silent Image _1st-level illusion_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5731
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a bit of fleece)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5735
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You create the image of an object, a creature, or some other visible "
"phenomenon that is no larger than a 15-foot cube. The image appears at a "
"spot within range and lasts for the duration. The image is purely visual; it "
"isn't accompanied by sound, smell, or other sensory effects.    \n"
"You can use your action to cause the image to move to any spot within "
"range. As the image changes location, you can alter its appearance so that "
"its movements appear natural for the image. For example, if you create an "
"image of a creature and move it, you can alter the image so that it appears "
"to be walking.    \n"
"Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an illusion, because "
"things can pass through it. A creature that uses its action to examine the "
"image can determine that it is an illusion with a successful Intelligence "
"(Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the "
"illusion for what it is, the creature can see through the image. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5737
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/simulacrum.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5742
msgid "name: Simulacrum level: 7 school: illusion classes: wizard"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5745
msgid "# Simulacrum _7th-level illusion_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5750
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 12 hours    \n"
"**Range:** Touch    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (snow or ice in quantities sufficient to made a "
"life-size copy of the duplicated creature; some hair, fingernail clippings, "
"or other piece of that creature's body placed inside the snow or ice; and "
"powdered ruby worth 1,500 gp, sprinkled over the duplicate and consumed by "
"the spell)    \n"
"**Duration:** Until dispelled \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5755
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You shape an illusory duplicate of one beast or humanoid that is within "
"range for the entire casting time of the spell. The duplicate is a creature, "
"partially real and formed from ice or snow, and it can take actions and "
"otherwise be affected as a normal creature. It appears to be the same as the "
"original, but it has half the creature's hit point maximum and is formed "
"without any equipment. Otherwise, the illusion uses all the statistics of "
"the creature it duplicates.    \n"
"The simulacrum is friendly to you and creatures you designate. It obeys your "
"spoken commands, moving and acting in accordance with your wishes and acting "
"on your turn in combat. The simulacrum lacks the ability to learn or become "
"more powerful, so it never increases its level or other abilities, nor can "
"it regain expended spell slots.    \n"
"If the simulacrum is damaged, you can repair it in an alchemical laboratory, "
"using rare herbs and minerals worth 100 gp per hit point it regains. The "
"simulacrum lasts until it drops to 0 hit points, at which point it reverts "
"to snow and melts instantly.    \n"
"If you cast this spell again, any currently active duplicates you created "
"with this spell are instantly destroyed. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5757
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/sleep.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5764
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Sleep\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: enchantment\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5767
msgid "# Sleep _1st-level enchantment_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5772
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 90 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a pinch of fine sand, rose petals, or a cricket)    "
"\n"
"**Duration:** 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5776
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This spell sends creatures into a magical slumber. Roll 5d8; the total is "
"how many hit points of creatures this spell can affect. Creatures within 20 "
"feet of a point you choose within range are affected in ascending order of "
"their current hit points (ignoring unconscious creatures).    \n"
"Starting with the creature that has the lowest current hit points, each "
"creature affected by this spell falls unconscious until the spell ends, the "
"sleeper takes damage, or someone uses an action to shake or slap the sleeper "
"awake. Subtract each creature's hit points from the total before moving on "
"to the creature with the next lowest hit points. A creature's hit points "
"must be equal to or less than the remaining total for that creature to be "
"affected.    \n"
"Undead and creatures immune to being charmed aren't affected by this "
"spell. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5778
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd "
"level or higher, roll an additional 2d8 for each slot level above 1st. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5780
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/sleet_storm.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5787
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Sleet Storm\n"
"level: 3\n"
"school: conjuration\n"
"classes: druid\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5790
msgid "# Sleet Storm _3rd-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5795
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 150 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a pinch of dust and a few drops of water)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5799
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Until the spell ends, freezing rain and sleet fall in a 20-foot-tall "
"cylinder with a 40-foot radius centered on a point you choose within "
"range. The area is heavily obscured, and exposed flames in the area are "
"doused.    \n"
"The ground in the area is covered with slick ice, making it difficult "
"terrain. When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a "
"turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a "
"failed save, it falls prone.    \n"
"If a creature is concentrating in the spell's area, the creature must make a "
"successful Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC or lose "
"concentration. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5801
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/slow.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5807
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Slow\n"
"level: 3\n"
"school: transmutation\n"
"classes: sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5810
msgid "# Slow _3rd-level transmutation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5815
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 120 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a drop of molasses)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5820
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You alter time around up to six creatures of your choice in a 40-foot cube "
"within range. Each target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or be "
"affected by this spell for the duration.    \n"
"An affected target's speed is halved, it takes a −2 penalty to AC and "
"Dexterity saving throws, and it can't use reactions. On its turn, it can use "
"either an action or a bonus action, not both. Regardless of the creature's "
"abilities or magic items, it can't make more than one melee or ranged attack "
"during its turn.    \n"
"If the creature attempts to cast a spell with a casting time of 1 action, "
"roll a d20. On an 11 or higher, the spell doesn't take effect until the "
"creature's next turn, and the creature must use its action on that turn to "
"complete the spell. If it can't, the spell is wasted.    \n"
"A creature affected by this spell makes another Wisdom saving throw at the "
"end of its turn. On a successful save, the effect ends for it. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5822
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/spare_the_dying.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5827
msgid "name: Spare the Dying level: 0 school: necromancy classes: cleric"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5830
msgid "# Spare the Dying _Necromancy cantrip_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5837
msgid ""
"You touch a living creature that has 0 hit points. The creature becomes "
"stable. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5839
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/speak_with_animals.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5846
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Speak with Animals\n"
"level: 1\n"
"school: divination\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         druid\n"
"         ranger\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5849
msgid "# Speak with Animals _1st-level divination (ritual)_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5856
msgid ""
"You gain the ability to comprehend and verbally communicate with beasts for "
"the duration. The knowledge and awareness of many beasts is limited by their "
"intelligence, but at minimum, beasts can give you information about nearby "
"locations and monsters, including whatever they can perceive or have "
"perceived within the past day. You might be able to persuade a beast to "
"perform a small favor for you, at the GM's discretion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5859
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/speak_with_dead.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5865
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Speak with Dead\n"
"level: 3\n"
"school: necromancy\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         cleric\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5868
msgid "# Speak with Dead _3rd-level necromancy_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5873
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 10 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (burning incense)    \n"
"**Duration:** 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5876
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You grant the semblance of life and intelligence to a corpse of your choice "
"within range, allowing it to answer the questions you pose. The corpse must "
"still have a mouth and can't be undead. The spell fails if the corpse was "
"the target of this spell within the last 10 days.    \n"
"Until the spell ends, you can ask the corpse up to five questions. The "
"corpse knows only what it knew in life, including the languages it "
"knew. Answers are usually brief, cryptic, or repetitive, and the corpse is "
"under no compulsion to offer a truthful answer if you are hostile to it or "
"it recognizes you as an enemy. This spell doesn't return the creature's soul "
"to its body, only its animating spirit. Thus, the corpse can't learn new "
"information, doesn't comprehend anything that has happened since it died, "
"and can't speculate about future events.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5878
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/speak_with_plants.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5885
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Speak with Plants\n"
"level: 3\n"
"school: transmutation\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         druid\n"
"         ranger\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5888
msgid "# Speak with Plants _3rd-level transmutation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5893
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Self (30-foot radius)    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5899
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You imbue plants within 30 feet of you with limited sentience and animation, "
"giving them the ability to communicate with you and follow your simple "
"commands. You can question plants about events in the spell's area within "
"the past day, gaining information about creatures that have passed, weather, "
"and other circumstances.    \n"
"You can also turn difficult terrain caused by plant growth (such as thickets "
"and undergrowth) into ordinary terrain that lasts for the duration. Or you "
"can turn ordinary terrain where plants are present into difficult terrain "
"that lasts for the duration, causing vines and branches to hinder pursuers, "
"for example.    \n"
"Plants might be able to perform other tasks on your behalf, at the GM's "
"discretion. The spell doesn't enable plants to uproot themselves and move "
"about, but they can freely move branches, tendrils, and stalks.    \n"
"If a plant creature is in the area, you can communicate with it as if you "
"shared a common language, but you gain no magical ability to influence it.    "
"\n"
"This spell can cause the plants created by the **_entangle_** spell to "
"release a restrained creature. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5901
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/spider_climb.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5908
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Spider Climb\n"
"level: 2\n"
"school: transmutation\n"
"classes: sorcerer\n"
"         warlock\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5911
msgid "# Spider Climb _2nd-level transmutation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5916
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Touch    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a drop of bitumen and a spider)   \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 hour \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5918
msgid ""
"Until the spell ends, one willing creature you touch gains the ability to "
"move up, down, and across vertical surfaces and upside down along ceilings, "
"while leaving its hands free. The target also gains a climbing speed equal "
"to its walking speed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5920
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/spike_growth.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5926
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Spike Growth\n"
"level: 2\n"
"school: transmutation\n"
"classes: druid\n"
"         ranger\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5929
msgid "# Spike Growth _2nd-level transmutation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5934
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 150 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (seven sharp thorns or seven small twigs, each "
"sharpened to a point)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5937
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The ground in a 20-foot radius centered on a point within range twists and "
"sprouts hard spikes and thorns. The area becomes difficult terrain for the "
"duration. When a creature moves into or within the area, it takes 2d4 "
"piercing damage for every 5 feet it travels.   \n"
"The transformation of the ground is camouflaged to look natural. Any "
"creature that can't see the area at the time the spell is cast must make a "
"Wisdom (Perception) check against your spell save DC to recognize the "
"terrain as hazardous before entering it. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5939
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/spirit_guardians.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5944
msgid "name: Spirit Guardians level: 3 school: conjuration classes: cleric"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5947
msgid "# Spirit Guardians _3rd-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5952
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Self (15-foot radius)    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a holy symbol)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5955
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You call forth spirits to protect you. They flit around you to a distance of "
"15 feet for the duration. If you are good or neutral, their spectral form "
"appears angelic or fey (your choice). If you are evil, they appear "
"fiendish.    \n"
"When you cast this spell, you can designate any number of creatures you can "
"see to be unaffected by it. An affected creature's speed is halved in the "
"area, and when the creature enters the area for the first time on a turn or "
"starts its turn there, it must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, "
"the creature takes 3d8 radiant damage (if you are good or neutral) or 3d8 "
"necrotic damage (if you are evil). On a successful save, the creature takes "
"half as much damage. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5957
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 4th "
"level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above "
"3rd. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5959
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/spiritual_weapon.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5964
msgid "name: Spiritual Weapon level: 2 school: evocation classes: cleric"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5967
msgid "# Spiritual Weapon _2nd-level evocation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5972
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 bonus action    \n"
"**Range:** 60 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5976
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You create a floating, spectral weapon within range that lasts for the "
"duration or until you cast this spell again. When you cast the spell, you "
"can make a melee spell attack against a creature within 5 feet of the "
"weapon. On a hit, the target takes force damage equal to 1d8 + your "
"spellcasting ability modifier.    \n"
"As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the weapon up to 20 feet and "
"repeat the attack against a creature within 5 feet of it.    \n"
"The weapon can take whatever form you choose. Clerics of deities who are "
"associated with a particular weapon (as St. Cuthbert is known for his mace "
"and Thor for his hammer) make this spell's effect resemble that weapon. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5978
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**At Higher Levels.** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd "
"level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for every two slot levels above "
"2nd. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5980
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/stinking_cloud.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5987
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Stinking Cloud\n"
"level: 3\n"
"school: conjuration\n"
"classes: bard\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5990
msgid "# Stinking Cloud _3rd-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5995
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** 90 feet    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (a rotten egg or several skunk cabbage leaves)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:5999
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"You create a 20-foot-radius sphere of yellow, nauseating gas centered on a "
"point within range. The cloud spreads around corners, and its area is "
"heavily obscured. The cloud lingers in the air for the duration.    \n"
"Each creature that is completely within the cloud at the start of its turn "
"must make a Constitution saving throw against poison. On a failed save, the "
"creature spends its action that turn retching and reeling. Creatures that "
"don't need to breathe or are immune to poison automatically succeed on this "
"saving throw.    \n"
"A moderate wind (at least 10 miles per hour) disperses the cloud after 4 "
"rounds. A strong wind (at least 20 miles per hour) disperses it after 1 "
"round. \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6001
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/stone_shape.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6008
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Stone Shape\n"
"level: 4\n"
"school: transmutation\n"
"classes: cleric\n"
"         druid\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6011
msgid "# Stone Shape _4th-level transmutation_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6016
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Touch    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (soft clay, which must be worked into roughly the "
"desired shape of the stone object)    \n"
"**Duration:** Instantaneous \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6018
msgid ""
"You touch a stone object of Medium size or smaller or a section of stone no "
"more than 5 feet in any dimension and form it into any shape that suits your "
"purpose. So, for example, you could shape a large rock into a weapon, idol, "
"or coffer, or make a small passage through a wall, as long as the wall is "
"less than 5 feet thick. You could also shape a stone door or its frame to "
"seal the door shut. The object you create can have up to two hinges and a "
"latch, but finer mechanical detail isn't possible."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6021
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/stoneskin.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6029
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"name: Stoneskin\n"
"level: 4\n"
"school: abjuration\n"
"classes: druid\n"
"         ranger\n"
"         sorcerer\n"
"         wizard\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6032
msgid "# Stoneskin _4th-level abjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6037
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Touch    \n"
"**Components:** V, S, M (diamond dust worth 100 gp, which the spell "
"consumes)    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 hour \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6039
msgid ""
"This spell turns the flesh of a willing creature you touch as hard as "
"stone. Until the spell ends, the target has resistance to nonmagical "
"bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6041
msgid "<!-- sources/spellcasting/spells/storm_of_vengeance.md -->"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6046
msgid "name: Storm of Vengeance level: 9 school: conjuration classes: druid"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6049
msgid "# Storm of Vengeance _9th-level conjuration_"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6054
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Casting Time:** 1 action    \n"
"**Range:** Sight    \n"
"**Components:** V, S    \n"
"**Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute \n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: translations/spells.merged.md:6061
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"A churning storm cloud forms, centered on a point you can see and spreading "
"to a radius of 360 feet. Lightning flashes in the area, thunder booms, and "
"strong winds roar. Each creature under the cloud (no more than 5,000 feet "
"beneath the cloud) when it appears must make a Constitution saving throw. On "
"a failed save, a creature takes 2d6 thunder damage and becomes deafened for "
"5 minutes.    \n"
"Each round you maintain concentration on this spell, the storm produces "
"additional effects on your turn.    \n"
"**Round 2.** Acidic rain falls from the cloud. Each creature and object "
"under the cloud takes 1d6 acid damage.    \n"
"**Round 3.** You call six bolts of lightning from the cloud to strike six "
"creatures or objects of your choice beneath the cloud. A given creature or "
"object can't be struck by more than one bolt. A struck creature must make a "
"Dexterity saving throw. The creature takes 10d6 lightning damage on a failed "
"save, or half as much damage on a successful one.    \n"
"**Round 4.** Hailstones rain down from the cloud. Each creature under the "
"cloud takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage.    \n"
"**Round 5–10.** Gusts and freezing rain assail the area under the cloud. The "
"area becomes difficult terrain and is heavily obscured. Each creature there "
"takes 1d6 cold damage. Ranged weapon attacks in the area are impossible. The "
"wind and rain count as a severe distraction for the purposes of maintaining "
"concentration on spells. Finally, gusts of strong wind (ranging from 20 to "
"50 miles per hour) automatically disperse fog, mists, and similar phenomena "
"in the area, whether mundane or magical.\n"
msgstr ""

